org.dexpi.pid.imaging.pidElements

Class ErrorElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dexpi.pid.imaging.pidElements.ErrorElement

  • public class ErrorElement
extends java.lang.Object
    An element that allows to depict an error. ID, componentName, compoentClass are specified by the ProteusXML 3.6.0 Schema. The subDescription allows to add further details about the error. Example for output in xml: <Error> <ID>1234</ID> <ComponentName>ISO Ball Valve</ComponentName> <ComponentClass>BallValve</ComponentClass> <LineNumber>827</LineNumber> <DetailedDescription> <Error Message="Line #828 - Cannot draw circle: color,line weight missing or incorrect."/> <Error Message="Line #839 - Cannot draw line: color,line weight missing or incorrect."/> <Error Message="Line #847 - Cannot draw line: color,line weight missing or incorrect."/> <Error Message="Line #855 - Cannot draw line: color,line weight missing or incorrect."/> <Error Message="Line #863 - Cannot draw line: color,line weight missing or incorrect."/> <Error Message="Line #871 - Cannot draw line: color,line weight missing or incorrect."/> <Error Message="Line #879 - Cannot draw line: color,line weight missing or incorrect."/> </DetailedDescription> </Error>
    Author:
    El Pulpo
